    "body": "Problem: `nvim_win_set_config` with `style=minimal` re-applies option values even if\r\nthe new style is unchanged from the old. This may be undesirable after https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/38122.\r\n\r\nSolution: don't bother in this case.\r\n\r\nSee https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/38122#issuecomment-3996994189.",
    "closed_at": "2026-03-09T18:28:37Z",
    "comment_data": [],
    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "OK, so this failed an existing test: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/22865#discussion_r1161598973.\r\n\r\nDiscussion on Matrix so far:\r\n- After clarifying the issue, bfredl considers the snippet in https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/38122#issuecomment-3996994189 an anti-pattern; existing intent is to update only the keys you want changed.\r\n- echasnovski prefers `nvim_win_set_config(0, nvim_win_get_config(0))` has no side-effects.\r\n- Personally I'm still in favour of the former, using `config.style = nil` if needed.\r\n- We weren't sure why ui2 does [this](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/563f9ef7994a35686419b4524cd772c97960dac1/runtime/lua/vim/_core/ui2.lua#L91); maybe it could've been replaced with a merge, or by updating specific keys? Maybe a good idea to not perform the initial `tbl_deep_extend` at all when replacing it too.\r\n- That said, not happy with the idea of reverting #38122. `style` does not _only_ apply at configure time; it's a saved value that has an effect for as long as it's set. It's very much a part of the window's config.\r\n- I _**jokingly**_ suggested waiting for #31903, adding `opts` to `nvim_win_get_config`, and making returning `style` opt-in. Hopefully that doesn't end up becoming a serious idea... :vomiting_face:\r\n\r\nHappy to instead document things as suggested in https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/38122#issuecomment-3997611800 if we can't reach consensus.",
            "created_at": "2026-03-04T14:55:37Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/38152#issuecomment-3998069597",
            "id": 3998069597,
            "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/issues/38152",
            "node_id": "IC_kwDOAPphoM7uTbNd",
