        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> echasnovski prefers nvim_win_set_config(0, nvim_win_get_config(0)) has no side-effects.\r\n\r\nSeems logical to me, though a bit dubious as bfredl mentioned. UI2 at least wants `nvim_open_win(0, nvim_win_get_config(0))` to open an identical window (at least in absence of #35816).\r\n\r\n> We weren't sure why ui2 does [this](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/563f9ef7994a35686419b4524cd772c97960dac1/runtime/lua/vim/_core/ui2.lua#L91); maybe it could've been replaced with a merge, or by updating specific keys? Maybe a good idea to not perform the initial tbl_deep_extend at all when replacing it too.\r\n\r\nThere are some dynamic options that UI2 wants to copy over to a new tabpage, recomputing the desired config could be done but would rather just copy the existing one. The `tbl_deep_extend` is indeed unnecessary (was just lazily avoiding an if/else), #38170 refactors it a bit.\r\n",
